HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 268
BY REPRESENTATIVE HEBERT
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 13, 2026, as Louisiana REALTORS
Day at the state capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, May 13, 2026, as Louisiana REALTORS Day at the state capitol
3 and to commend Louisiana REALTORS for more than a century of leadership in
4 advancing the American dream of homeownership.
5 WHEREAS, Louisiana REALTORS is a one-hundred-seven-year-old organization
6 with more than fifteen thousand members that has served as a trusted guide for Louisiana
7 families pursuing the American dream for over a century by helping them secure homes,
8 build equity, and establish lasting foundations for future generations; and
9 WHEREAS, across every parish of this great state, members of Louisiana
10 REALTORS serve on the front lines of opportunity to open doors not only to houses, but to
11 stability, independence, and the promise that hard work can still lead to a place to call your
12 own; and
13 WHEREAS, homeownership is a fundamental aspect of the American dream and
14 remains one of the most powerful and enduring ideals in our nation; it is rooted in the
15 fundamental right to own, use, and enjoy private property; Louisiana REALTORS plays a
16 vital role in keeping that dream alive and within reach; and
17 WHEREAS, the protection of private property rights is a cornerstone of the
18 Constitution of the United States and the Constitution of Louisiana; that protection forms the
19 legal and moral foundation on which economic freedom, individual liberty, and prosperity
20 are built; and
