6 professionalism and ethical conduct; these professionals ensure that families and businesses
7 are represented with integrity in transactions that often define their financial future; and
8 WHEREAS, real estate in Louisiana is a foundational component of the economic
9 strength of the state; it is the second-largest sector that contributes to the state's gross
10 domestic product and generates approximately $54 billion annually, which fuels prosperity
11 statewide; and
12 WHEREAS, real estate transactions create a powerful ripple effect that supports
13 mortgage lending, title professionals, contractors, small businesses, and countless Louisiana
14 workers whose livelihoods depend on a strong and stable housing market; and
15 WHEREAS, the real estate industry supports tens of thousands of jobs across
16 Louisiana; commercial real estate sustains more than sixty-three thousand jobs and
17 contributes meaningfully to wages and economic output; and
18 WHEREAS, Louisiana REALTORS serves as a key partner in economic
19 development by working alongside public officials and private leaders to attract investment,
20 support workforce housing, revitalize communities, and ensure that Louisiana remains
21 competitive in a rapidly evolving economy; and
22 WHEREAS, Louisiana is defined by its resilience in the face of hurricanes, flood
23 risks, and insurance challenges, and Louisiana REALTORS provides the expertise and
24 leadership necessary to help communities recover, rebuild, and grow stronger; and
25 WHEREAS, members of Louisiana REALTORS across the state demonstrate a deep
26 commitment to service, civic leadership, and volunteerism; Louisiana REALTORS invests
27 in property, people, and the long-term future of the state.
28 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
29 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, May 13, 2026, as Louisiana
30 REALTORS Day at the state capitol; does hereby commend Louisiana REALTORS for
